description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/5860/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'plug, inlet and outlet, for computer cable', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;This is a mobile infrastructure, representing the product of a typical set of plugs, inlet and outlet for an electric computer power cord. Its production represents a inlet plug with pins that has a mass of 0.0293 kg and 0.0292 kg for the outlet plug. It includes all materials necessary to construct it and energy consumption during manufacturing.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'plug, inlet and outlet, for computer cable',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of 'plug, inlet and outlet, for computer cable',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.
